{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-09T19:59:21.983364391Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-cc71f355","body":"The `validate_classification` function does not check individual entries in `affected_files` (FixNow variant) for empty or whitespace-only strings. A classification with `affected_files: vec![\"\".to_owned()]` passes validation. Add a check that rejects empty/whitespace-only entries in the affected_files vector, consistent with how all other string fields are validated.","dedup_key":"a957d2ae749a6ad601402c0192125a7d07ffb632b0eeaf5d13536471ab67388d","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260409194344","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":18,"timestamp":"2026-04-09T19:59:21.992512561Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-b63f9c8c","body":"src/contexts/workflow_composition/review_classification.rs:108-110 only rejects an empty `mapped_to_bead_id`, and the accompanying coverage at 350-360 exercises only that case. The bead contract says this field must be syntactically valid, but values such as `\"../bad\"`, `\"bad id\"`, or `\" 9ni.8.5.2 \"` currently pass `validate_classification()`. That lets malformed planned-elsewhere ownership references get serialized and carried forward until reconciliation, where they are indistinguishable from a legitimate-but-stale bead reference. Tighten validation (or normalize then validate) for bead-id syntax and add tests for malformed IDs.","dedup_key":"70731f99a40f531081a6a9980a9e815868ef64ebae13f5081ab43383d1278ce5","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260409194344","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
