{"sequence":70,"timestamp":"2026-04-09T20:35:36.485874140Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-4878e972","body":"`src/contexts/workflow_composition/review_classification.rs:49-76` does not reject unknown or cross-variant fields during deserialization. Because `FindingClassification` is an internally tagged enum without any `deny_unknown_fields` guard, a payload like `{\"classification\":\"fix-now\",...,\"mapped_to_bead_id\":\"bead-2\"}` will deserialize as `FixNow` and silently discard the planned-elsewhere field. That violates the stated rule that each finding must have exactly one classification and lets malformed reviewer output take the wrong downstream path instead of being rejected.","dedup_key":"ff5d40aa4888c58bfe74607066e903a42b22eec111eb151cf49ebac4d35902f7","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260409194344","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":71,"timestamp":"2026-04-09T20:35:36.495213349Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-673cabe8","body":"`src/contexts/workflow_composition/review_classification.rs:127-143` never validates `remediation_hint` when it is present on `FixNow`. `Some(\"\")` and whitespace-only hints currently pass `validate_classification`, even though the bead explicitly calls for rejecting malformed classifications and empty-string edge cases. That means persisted/classified findings can carry a meaningless remediation hint as if it were valid data.","dedup_key":"28ffc59fb3259a2b93407d99a25ab1c1b24aeb86432441849016b899a7af2482","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260409194344","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
